name: Man City
summary: In the EFL Cup, Tottenham Hotspur overcame Manchester City with Werner and Sarr scoring to advance to the quarterfinals. In other Premier League action, Manchester City narrowly defeated Southampton 1-0 with Erling Haaland scoring the deciding goal. Despite the win, City manager Pep Guardiola expressed concerns about the team's depth, citing only 13 players available. Speculation is rife that Manchester United are targeting a potential successor to Erik ten Hag with Manchester City's Guardiola being considered. Meanwhile, Guardiola has dismissed concerns of a collapse similar to what Manchester United experienced after his departure. In other news, Manchester City's Rodri has won the Ballon d'Or, edging out Real Madrid's Vinicius Jr.

summary: Rapper Young Thug has changed his plea to guilty in the ongoing RICO trial, marking a significant development in Georgia's longest-running criminal case. According to reports, Young Thug will be released on house arrest due to time served as part of a plea deal. The plea deal concludes the YSL RICO trial, with the lead defendant receiving a sentence in line with time already served. This outcome comes after multiple plea changes in the case, which has involved charges of gang activity, drug trafficking, and gun possession.

name: La Dodgers
summary: The Los Angeles Dodgers have emerged victorious in the 2024 World Series, claiming the championship title after a hard-fought Game 5 against the New York Yankees. The intense series, pitting two of baseball's most iconic franchises against each other, culminated in a nail-biting finale that witnessed the Dodgers' dramatic comeback. Despite claiming the championship, questions linger regarding the health of star player Shohei Ohtani, whose injury cast a shadow over their Game 2 triumph. Amidst the joy of victory, Los Angeles has witnessed isolated incidents of looting and violence. As the city revels in its team's success, it grapples with maintaining order and ensuring safety for all.

name: South Korea
summary: Tensions continue to escalate in the Korean peninsula and Eastern Europe. North Korea has sent its foreign minister to Russia as its troops train to aid Russia against Ukraine. South Korea has condemned Russia's move to seal a defense pact with North Korea, fearing their involvement in the conflict could have global implications. The U.S. and South Korea are concerned about the potential deployment of North Korean troops in Ukraine. France's BNP Paribas has been indicted by Korea for illegal short-selling, while Canada's Gushue has won the opening match of the Pan Continental curling championship against South Korea. South Korea is considering sending a team to Ukraine, while China is urged to play a "constructive" role amid the military cooperation between North Korea and Russia. South Korea is also exploring closer ties with the BRICS nations to expand its global reach.

name: Tottenham
summary: Tottenham Hotspur recently defeated Manchester City 2-1 in the EFL Cup thanks to a standout performance from one of its stars, as reported by Forbes. name: Josh Addo-Carr
summary: Australian rugby league player Josh Addo-Carr has been sacked by the Canterbury Bulldogs after failing a roadside drug test. Addo-Carr has expressed his regret over the incident, admitting that he came to the club at their lowest point. Despite hiring a top lawyer to fight for his job, the Bulldogs have ultimately decided to terminate his contract. This news comes as a crushing blow to Addo-Carr, leaving his NRL career in doubt. The Bulldogs have reportedly made a move to replace Addo-Carr with another player, while the Sydney Morning Herald has linked another star player, Ryan Papenhuyzen, with a move to the club. Addo-Carr has thanked Bulldogs fans for their support and expressed his intention to move forward from this setback.

name: Trick-or-treat
summary: This Halloween, trick-or-treating enthusiasts will have to navigate varying weather conditions across Canada. While some regions, such as Calgary, Victoria, and Coquitlam, anticipate favorable conditions for outdoor festivities, others, including Syracuse and Vancouver, could experience rain or colder temperatures. Notably, Des Moines, Iowa, will allow trick-or-treating on Halloween itself for the first time since 1938. To ensure a safe and enjoyable experience, BarrieToday highlights an accessible Halloween Village that offers a trick-or-treating experience. Additionally, CBC.ca raises the question of whether trick-or-treating should be moved to the weekend for convenience and safety, while CTV News provides a comprehensive forecast for Halloween weather across the country.
